gene check_vlan_trunk
  is diagnostic
  risk none

  does:
    Check VLAN trunk connectivity by verifying that expected
    VLANs are configured on the trunk interface and that
    traffic can pass through.

  takes:
    trunk_interface  string  "Trunk interface name"
    expected_vlans   int[]   "Expected VLAN IDs"

  gives:
    success    bool     "Overall health status"
    healthy    bool     "Whether trunk is healthy"
    vlans_ok   int[]    "VLANs that are configured correctly"
    vlans_missing int[] "VLANs that are missing"

  before:
    trunk interface must exist

  after:
    no side effects â€” diagnostic only

  fails when:
    trunk interface does not exist
    trunk interface is not configured as a trunk
